imotif analysis: making heatmap with selected proteins/experiments

01 March, 2023

  • Libraries
  • read data
  • plot heatmap, selected data
  • heatmap scaled data, with row-split, selected experiments

Libraries

suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(ComplexHeatmap))
suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(circlize))
library(RColorBrewer)

read data

myfile<-'imotif_array_v2.median_SNR.avg_reps.tab'
all_data<-read.csv(myfile,sep="\t")

plot heatmap, selected data

mycolors<-RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(10,"Set3")
names(mycolors) <- sort(unique(all_data$SeqClass))
data_mat<-as.matrix(all_data[,c(3:ncol(all_data))])

selected<-c("iMab100nM_6.5_40","Mx2nM_6.5_40","hnRNPK","hnRNPLL","hnRNPA1", "ASF")
data_mat<-data_mat[,selected]

colnames(data_mat)[1:2]<-c('iMab','Mitoxantrone')
rownames(data_mat)<-all_data$New_ID
scaled_data<-scale(data_mat)



col_fun = colorRamp2(c(-3, 0, 3), c("blue","white", "red"))

row_ha = rowAnnotation(Sequence_class=all_data$SeqClass,
                       col=list(Sequence_class=mycolors)
)

Heatmap(scaled_data, 
        cluster_rows = T, 
        cluster_columns = T, 
        name="Zscore", 
        show_column_dend = T , 
        show_row_dend = F, 
        show_column_names = T , 
        show_row_names =F,  
        right_annotation = row_ha,
        column_title ="", 
        col = col_fun,
        row_title_rot = 0)

pdf("figs/all_data_combined_avg_reps.scaled.rowsplit.heatmap.SELECTED.pdf", width = 5, height=8)

Heatmap(scaled_data, 
        cluster_rows = T, 
        cluster_columns = T, 
        name="Zscore", 
        show_column_dend = T , 
        show_row_dend = F, 
        show_column_names = T , 
        show_row_names =F,  
        right_annotation = row_ha,
        column_title ="", 
        col = col_fun,
        row_title_rot = 0)
dev.off()
## quartz_off_screen 
##                 2

heatmap scaled data, with row-split, selected experiments

pdf("figs/all_data_combined_avg_reps.scaled.rowsplit.heatmap.SELECTED.pdf", width = 5, height=8)
Heatmap(scaled_data, 
        cluster_rows = T, 
        cluster_columns = T, 
        name="Zscore", 
        show_column_dend = T , 
        show_row_dend = F, 
        show_column_names = T , 
        show_row_names =F,  
        right_annotation = row_ha,
        row_split = all_data$SeqClass,
        column_title ="", 
        col = col_fun,
        row_title_gp=gpar(fontsize=8),
        row_title_rot = 0)

dev.off()
